race.comment: LADY VERITY (11) resumes for her second campaign having run two good races last time in, just finding one better on both occasions, beaten half a length at Sale before a spell. She's a well bred filly by I Am Invincible out of a G1 winning mare and with natural improvement this time in she can get the job done. DIHHERI (10) is a filly by Royal Meeting on debut for the Kennewell yard. She's won both hitouts leading in and looks ready to go. Respect any market moves. RED BARRON (6) is off a long spell here having contested a pair of strong 2yo races when last seen. The betting will be key with him. CUISINE (9) resumes having been solid on debut here. Expect the stable have her ready to go.
